<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-11T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-11T05:00:00-05:00" n="907" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d907">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/741: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kelley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-11T13:00:00+03:00">October
                                    11, 1942—1 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 2:29 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1008. Embassy’s 951, September 24, paragraph 1. Embassy obtained
                            possession today of the 3 bomb sights and other secret instruments which
                            were part of the equipment of the 3 United States Army bombers interned
                            in the Ankara airport. Arrangements have been made to obtain the bomb
                            sight and secret instruments in the bomber interned at Arifiye upon the
                            conclusion of the holidays here. As soon as the Embassy has obtained
                            possession of all the instruments I shall forward them by special
                            courier to the appropriate authorities in Lydda.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Kelley</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>